---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Granny Flats Seaford | Coastal Spec, Beach-Access Suburbs | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Granny flat builders for Seaford — coastal AS 4312 salt-zone spec, mix of older fibro and new builds, Frankston City Council. 1-bed, 2-bed and garden studios. Free consultation."
  canonical="https://frankstongrannyflats.com.au/seaford/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Seaford &middot; Seaford Wetlands &middot; Belvedere</span>
      <h1>Granny flats in <span class="accent">Seaford</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Seaford is the northern coastal end of Frankston City &mdash; beach access via
        the station, mix of older fibro cottages and 1990s brick-veneer. Granny flat
        demand here is mostly adult children + rental supplementary income. Salt-zone
        spec applies west of the railway line.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free consultation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Seaford</span>
      <h2>The Seaford granny flat story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>

      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>The salt-zone line runs through Seaford.</h3>
        <p>
          The AS 4312 moderate-to-severe salt-spray zone extends roughly 3km inland
          from Port Phillip Bay. For Seaford, that line runs east of Nepean Highway
          &mdash; meaning blocks west of the railway and Nepean Highway need coastal
          spec (stainless fittings, marine-grade sealants, hot-dip-galvanised steel)
          while blocks east of the railway are typically inland-spec. We do an
          AS 4312 distance check at site visit.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Older block, older services.</h3>
        <p>
          A lot of Seaford&rsquo;s housing stock is 1950s and 1960s &mdash; meaning the
          existing services (water main, sewer connection, electrical switchboard)
          are often undersized for a second dwelling. We do a services audit at the
          design stage so the $5,000&ndash;$15,000 cost of upgrading switchboard,
          sub-board, and sewer junction is in the fixed quote, not a surprise at
          construction.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Rental income market.</h3>
        <p>
          Seaford rental yields are healthy &mdash; 1-bedroom self-contained units in
          Seaford rent for $400&ndash;$520/week long-term, which makes a $130K modular
          granny flat pay back in 6&ndash;8 years before considering capital gain. We
          design Seaford granny flats with the &ldquo;future tenant&rdquo; spec in mind
          &mdash; full kitchen, separate laundry, separate entry, separately-metered
          electricity and water where possible.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Seaford jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>1-bedroom 45m&sup2; modular for long-term rental, $120K&ndash;$155K coastal-spec</li>
          <li>Adult-child accommodation with separate-meter rental option later</li>
          <li>Garden studio with optional bathroom (future-rental-flexible), $50K&ndash;$85K</li>
          <li>Switchboard upgrade + sub-board install (older Seaford property baseline)</li>
          <li>Coastal-spec inspection package (post-build certification)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/frankston-south/">Frankston South</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mt-eliza/">Mt Eliza</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mornington/">Mornington</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/carrum-downs/">Carrum Downs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mornington-peninsula/">Mornington Peninsula</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Seaford design consultation.</h2>
        <p>Salt-zone check, services audit, future-rental-flexible design.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
